<item>
  <title>HOW DOES CHANGING IN COACHES AFFECT A RANKING OF A TEAM</title>
  <dc:creator>Noora Mohamed</dc:creator>
  <link>https://your-website-url.example.com/posts/real-madrids-manager-woes/</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 





<p>The results of a game, is a reflection of how a coaching is doing behind closed doors. Coaches are expected to train, discipline and prepare their athletes for every possibility in the field.</p>
<p>Fans focus on the winning and scoring, the real impact all comes back through the planning and knowledge, that coaches implant in their players.</p>
<p>The score of a single game, leads back to the training that happens before a game, and how much effort is put into the players, revealing the ability the coach has when it comes to a team performance.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/the-club/history/football-legends/alvaro-arbeloa-coca">Álvaro Arbeloa</a>, a professional Spanish former defender football player and current manager of Real Madrid. Arbeloa has won many trophies; Club World Cup, a UEFA Super Cup, a LaLiga Title, two Copas del Rey and a Spanish Super Cup. His ability to train young athelets, has proven what a person really learns and teaches others has an imapct.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/the-club/history/football-legends/xabier-alonso-olano">Xabi Alonso</a> a former Midfielder football player and a former coach in Real Madrid. Alonso has played in about 236 competitive games, wining over 9 trophies during his time as a football player, his trophies included one LaLiga title and two European Championships with Spain. Alonso is considered as one of the best midfilers of his generations.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/latest-news/ancelotti-18-12-2024">Carlo Ancellotti</a>, the former coach of Real Madrid, is one of the ost decorated coach in the history of Real Madrid, wining over 15 trophies. Ancellotti has started his career in July 2009, coaching AC Milan for eight years. Before transitioning into</p>
<p><strong>How much does a change of coach play in team ranking?</strong></p>
