<p>For my hypothesis, I used ESPN to analyze and understand how coaching change, has an impact on the team’s skills and ranking. After, studying the bar charts, I discovered that a team player’s performance and ranking, demonstrates the skills and proficiency of the coach.</p>
<p>For instance, Dean Huijsen is a Defender for Real Madrid during the LaLiga season he was number one ranked, when he was coached by Alvaro Arbeloa, who was also a former defender player. The bar chart results, demonstrates that when a coach changes it can in fact have an impact on team performances, which is very to important to understand that when coaches apply their experience on young athletes the field, the results speak louder.</p>
